The paper focuses on generating visualizations from datasets, which is a common problem in computer graphics (cs.GR). It also involves working with large datasets and preserving important properties, which are common challenges in database systems (cs.DB). The use of sampling algorithms and optimization techniques suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions bar charts, which are a common type of visualization in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the focus on preserving visual properties of interest to analysts suggests a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
